gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Lakers 123, Bucks 122
gameRecap.excerpt: Spencer Dinwiddie blocked a Damian Lillard jumper as time expired as the Lakers held on to win the game. DAngelo Russell led the Lakers with a season-high 44 points and nine 3PM, along with nine assists, and six rebounds as the Lakers defeated the Bucks, 123-122. Russell caught fire in Q4, with 21 points on 8-11 shooting and 4-6 3PT. He scored the final eight points for the Lakers. Anthony Davis added 22 points, 13 rebounds, five assists, and three blocks in the win. Giannis Antetokoumpo led the Bucks with the 8th triple double of the season and 43rd of his career, which ties him with Fat Lever for 12th-most all-time as Damian Lillard added 28 points and 12 assists. The Lakers move to the 9th seed as they improve to 35-30 while the Bucks fall to 41-23 and go to the third seed, with Cleveland overtaking them.
